On the UX side, I don't think we did enough to plan for the growth and anticipate years

473
00:28:04,533 --> 00:28:08,674
of growth of features being added to our game and needing to add them to the core loop.

474
00:28:09,054 --> 00:28:13,396
And each feature we just have to do more like UX refactoring to make sure it really works

475
00:28:13,776 --> 00:28:15,096
and that it's surfaced to the player.

476
00:28:15,376 --> 00:28:16,457
And I think this is natural.

477
00:28:16,517 --> 00:28:18,818
There's just like, you know...

478
00:28:19,898 --> 00:28:24,621
There was no way to not have stat inflation in our game over time and power creep over time,

479
00:28:24,641 --> 00:28:28,323
and it's a challenge just to plan for it and make sure to provide a great user experience.

480
00:28:28,683 --> 00:28:33,206
I don't think it's possible to grow your game's feature depth over three years

481
00:28:33,366 --> 00:28:35,928
and not need this sort of refactoring over time,

482
00:28:36,248 --> 00:28:38,329
but I think better planning for it at the outset

483
00:28:38,649 --> 00:28:42,512
would have made our lives easier in presenting great features to players over time.

484
00:28:43,471 --> 00:28:46,092
